An unsuccessful siege of the Jasna Gora Monastery during this conflict stiffened
resistance by one side, which formed the Confederation of Tyszowce. Janusz Radziwill
switched sides in this conflict by signing the Union of (+) Kedainiai. This conflict was
ended by the Peace of Oliva and the Truce of Andrusovo and began with an uprising of
Zaphorozian Cossacks which cost one side control of Ukraine, the (*) Khmelnytsky Uprising.
Hetman Stefan Czarniecki helped John Casimir II drive out the invading armies of Alexis I and Charles
X in this conflict. For the points, name this devastating Russian and Swedish invasion which broke the
power of Poland-Lithuania.=====
